PURPOSE:-
--------
I/ITSEC 2003 demo scenario using the QualNet HLA interface.

SCENARIO:-
---------
I/ITSEC 2003 demo scenario using the QualNet HLA interface.  The scenario
consists of 27 nodes comprising:

- 4 platoon networks consisting of four tanks each
- 1 company network consisting of four platoon leaders
- 1 bent-pipe satellite link connecting the company commander to the
  Battalion HQ
- A wired backbone consisting of a Battalion HQ, Brigade HQ, and Division HQ
- A wireless link from the Division HQ to a UAV.

AODV is used to route throughout the network.

RUN:-
----
Run "<QUALNET_HOME>/bin/qualnet iitsec.config".

DESCRIPTION OF THE FILES:-
-------------------------
1. iitsec.app - QualNet configuration file for application input.
2. iitsec.config - QualNet configuration input file (no GUI hierarchies).
3. iitsec.hla-entities - QualNet configuration file listing entity
   marking strings to monitor.
4. iitsec.hla-radios - QualNet configuration file mapping entity
   marking strings to nodeIds.
5. iitsec.hla-networks - QualNet configuration file listing networks
   eligible for communication effects requests.
6. iitsec.nodes - QualNet node position file.
7. iitsec.router-models - QualNet router models file.
8. iitsec.router-static - QualNet static routes file.
9. iitsec-hier.config - QualNet configuration input file (GUI hierarchies).
10. iitsec-slow.config - QualNet configuration input file (slow radios).
11. RPR-FOM.fed - RPR FOM 1.0 FED file.
12. STRIVE-RPR.fed - STRIVE RPR-FOM 1.0 FED file.
13. README - This file.
